result.name: The Hunt Coffee & Roastery

reviews.text: The Hunt is a rather pleasant place in Kwun Tong, an industrial area, busy and noisy with constant road traffic. Their menu is rather extensive, and it lists seven "home made" desserts which we didn't try, sadly. We ordered a small mocha and small hot chocolate. And small is actually an understatement, it was actually a tiny serving. But it tasted quite good, but nothing close to great. Service was friendly.

We had a luncheon meeting in the fine restaurant first time.   I am in F&B business for 15 years.   I reckon this is one fine restaurant with the right elements in respect of service,  raw material and cuisine cooking recipe.

We had high score for all the food except the coffee.   Coffee there is a total disaster for some reason.
very nice for a drink & meal. spacious & comfy seatings. reasonable price.
The food is great , I especially like the burger which is juicy and soft! However the price is also not cheap for this location. Generally it worths it but just be prepared to pay the bill!
Good place for chill out
